olive oil
1 packet Crumbed Chicken Breast Strips
1 Wholemeal Panini
1 tomato
1 avocado
1 cucumber
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 packet Italian Truffle Mayonnaise

• Heat frying pan over medium-high
heat with enough olive oil to coat the
base of the pan
• Cook chicken until golden and cooked
through, 3-4 mins each side. Season
and set aside
• Meanwhile, halve panini and toast or
grill to your liking

• Thinly slice tomato, cucumber and
avocado (1/2 for 2P / 1 for 4P)

• In a bowl, combine mixed salad
leaves, cucumber and balsamic
dressing. Season
• Spread panini with some truffle
mayonnaise. Top with chicken,
avocado and tomato
• Serve with salad